///////////Package.json/////////
> Entry Point to application
> script (start stop build)
> metadata (version, name, author)
> packages

/////////////
Step to generate a package.json
///////
** NodeJs must be install
> open cmd/terminal and go inside folder
> npm init
> answer all question
> type yes


/////////////
Step to install package
///////
> ** NodeJs must be install
> go inside the folder
> npm i packagename / npm install packagename / npm i packagename --save

/////////////
Step to uninstall package
///////
> go inside the folder
> npm uninstall packagename


/////////////
Step to install dev dependency
///////
> go inside the folder
> npm i packagename --save-dev


/////////////
Step to install global dependency
///////
# install in laptop (c drive)
# its not specific to folder
# use for start/build/test
# very few dependency go global
# we need admin access to install global dependency

#window
> open cmd as administrator
> npm i -g packagename
> close cmd

#mac/linux
> open terminal
> sudo npm i -g packagename


